  "prompt": "Is Niacin added in the preparation of cannabis?",
  "response": "The preparation of cannabis typically does not involve the addition of niacin (vitamin B3). Cannabis products mainly focus on the plant's cannabinoids (such as THC and CBD), terpenes, and other natural compounds inherent to cannabis. \n\nHowever, cannabis products can sometimes be infused with additional vitamins, nutrients, or supplements for various formulations designed for specific effects or health benefits, although this practice is not very common. If you are looking for a product with additional vitamins such as niacin, it would be best to check the specific labels or product claims of individual cannabis products from manufacturers or dispensaries to see if such ingredients are included.",
